Maven is a build tool for java applications. we will get the dependencies files of java appl by using maven.
Once everything is done we will deploy the application in Apache TomCat
there are 7 commands in maven life cycle. 
First we have to install maven
apt install maven -y ---for ubuntu machines
and then to verify its version use mvn -v
maven lifecycle: 
1. mvn validate
2. mvn compile
3. mvn test
4. mvn package
5. mvn install or mvn clean install --- by using this command we will download all jar and war files in the project
6. mvn verify
7. mvn deploy


after installing all the available files into our system we have to deploy this application in Apache Tomcat 
